$ Excel: Home -> Styles -> Conditional Formatting -> New Rule

Rule types that can be selected:
table { ll
  Format all cells based on their values ☰
  Format only cells that contain ☰
  Format only top or bottom ranked values ☰
  Format only values that are obove or below average ☰
  Format only unique or duplicate values ☰
  use a → Microsoft/Office/Excel/formulas[formula] to determine which cells to format ☰
table }
